In this workshop, jewelry designer Alix Bluh will show you a simple crochet stitch for beading that offers endless options for customization by using different thread and bead combinations. You&rsquo;ll also learn how to create different style clasps, and incorporate leather for a less time-intensive project that achieves the same sophisticated look. The fundamentals that you&rsquo;ll learn in this class can be endlessly adapted to achieve different looks depending on the color thread and gems you chose.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Note: In this class, Alix uses an unconventional crocheted chain stitch to create the foundation chain for her jewelry. While this nontraditional stitch works fine for this class, new crocheters may be interested in learning how to work a traditional chain stitch. Watch Edie Eckman&#39;s class on this topic <a href="https://www.creativebug.com/classseries/single/how-to-work-a-crochet-chain">here</a>.&nbsp;
